The paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their hybridization with recurrent networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of soft weights and neural architecture search (NAS), which are common topics in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of algorithmic tasks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
